content.description: This is a beautiful overhanging granite face. Sit start on a good crimp. Work your way up on progressively worse crimps until your reach the lip, a spectacular jug rail.
content.protection: On the right side of the main wall. Start on the block a few feet right of the small arete.
content.location: Have at least two pads and a spotter

content.description: This is a beautiful overhanging granite face. Stand start on a good crimp. Work your way up on progressively worse crimps until your reach the lip, a spectacular jug rail.
content.protection: Have at least two pads and a spotter
content.location: On the right side of the main wall. Start on the block a few feet right of the small arete.

content.description: Start with your hands on the enormous horizontal granite flake. Then make a burly deadpoint for a shallow dish on the lip. Work your feet up and top out with whatever you've got.
content.location: Left side of the main wall

content.description: This route is short but technical. Layback the finger crack working your feet up until you can reach positive holds over the lip. Then mantle your way over the top.
content.location: The obvious finger crack in the corner

content.description: This small granite quarry is an isolated island of rock amidst a forest overgrown. It is ideal escape from the claustrophobia of bushwhacking through the brush because it is open to both the air and the sun.
